org.jcvi.jillion.experimental.align.blast

Class XmlFileBlastParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.experimental.align.blast.XmlFileBlastParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BlastParser

    public final class XmlFileBlastParser
extends Object
implements BlastParser
    XmlFileBlastParser is a BlastParser implementation that can parse XML formatted Blast output (-m 7). This class should work on both nucleotide and protein alignments.
    Author:
    dkatzel

      • canParse

        public boolean canParse()
        Description copied from interface: BlastParser
        Can the parser (re)parse the blast output. Some implementations may only be able to parse the output a few times (or even only once). This method allows clients to programatically check if a call to BlastParser.parse(BlastVisitor) will fail.
        Specified by:
        canParse in interface BlastParser
        Returns:
        true if BlastParser.parse(BlastVisitor) can be called without throwing an IllegalStateException; false otherwise.
